main event: On 17 January 1966, two white objects were observed flying side-by-side with a bright tail pointed downward for 3-5 minutes before suddenly disappearing.
interesting points: The objects were flying in a slow downward motion., The tail of the objects was described as bright and pointing downward., The sighting duration of 3-5 minutes rules out a meteor explanation., The observation was made by a civilian source., No physical evidence or photographs were recorded.
witness description: A3c P. C. Collier, an NCO Observer
